text
@d1 1
a1 1
%META:TOPICINFO{author="ArlinStoltzfus" date="1286477704" format="1.1" version="1.17"}%
d29 1
a29 1
But this is not the case.  Of these millions of trees, a tiny fraction is published in the form of a graphical images interpretable only to a human reader.  To a computer, such trees are informational dead-ends.  
